                            <comment id="13669229" author="msahyoun" created="Wed, 29 May 2013 13:23:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Tom,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;that seems to be an issue introduced in the 1.8.x release. Worked on 1.7.x. It&apos;s not because of the splitting itself as if you simply load and save the original file using 1.8.x the issue occurs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We will need to investigate which change caused that regression.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;BR&lt;br/&gt;
Maruan&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13669325" author="jmkgreen" created="Wed, 29 May 2013 14:58:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Per mailing list post we are now tracking this as it affects both old and new Overlay tools.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13669423" author="lehmi" created="Wed, 29 May 2013 16:47:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I guess I found a first hint for a solution. The lookup table of the indexed colorspace is altered. I&apos;m investigating ...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13669458" author="lehmi" created="Wed, 29 May 2013 17:14:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-1437&quot; title=&quot;Title invalidly read in DocumentInformation&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-1437&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-1437&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; introduced the regression. The written COSString uses UTF-16 instead of a simple hex string for the lookup table (see COSString#getString)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13669466" author="lehmi" created="Wed, 29 May 2013 17:28:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I found the problem and fixed it in revision 1487557. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, should we cancel the vote to integrate this one?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13669486" author="msahyoun" created="Wed, 29 May 2013 17:47:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think that would be good to do as there are already reports of that behavior&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;BR&lt;br/&gt;
Maruan&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13669512" author="lehmi" created="Wed, 29 May 2013 18:01:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I canceled the vote and will integrate the solution into 1.8.2&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13669535" author="jmkgreen" created="Wed, 29 May 2013 18:20:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks guys - likely to be raised as a blocker bug for us in our product meeting tomorrow morning so be good to report an imminent fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13670143" author="tomtaylor" created="Thu, 30 May 2013 07:54:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the quick work! Any estimate of when 1.8.2 goes to release?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13670147" author="msahyoun" created="Thu, 30 May 2013 08:00:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Tom,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1.8.2 is in the voting process and should be available next week provided that the vote passes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;BR&lt;br/&gt;
Maruan&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
